> Looking for a super quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Super Quick Cajun Beef Bowl in just 15 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the saucepan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks.

Meanwhile, cut the @Avocado{1} into chunks.

Drain the fat from the mince. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Next, stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water{125%ml}.

Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Share the rice between bowls and spoon over the Cajun beef.

Top with the avocado.

Sprinkle over the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} and drizzle with @Soured Cream{75%g}.

Enjoy!